Kampimodromus aberrans

is a very common species in orchards, vineyards and wild plants in Europe and in North-Africa where it might be closely associated with several species of spider and eriophyid mites (
Duso 1992
; 
Schausberger 1997
; 

Tixier 
et al.
1998

, 2000a, b; 

Kreiter 
et al.
2000

; 
Tsolakis and Ragusa 2017
).

This species has been mentioned previously from Slovenia ( Miklavc 2006 ; Bohinc and Trdan 2013 ;
Bohinc et al. 2018
). With 324 specimens in total in 13 locations, it is one of the most commonly species found in this survey.
